= The Budget Is the Map

A city budget is one of the most valuable documents available to researchers, entrepreneurs, consultants, nonprofits, and community leaders.

The budget reveals:

- What problems exist
- What priorities leaders have identified
- Which departments are responsible
- How much money is available
- Which projects are currently funded
- Which initiatives may need partners

